brief_summary.textblock:
      This is a single arm, open label, phase II study to evaluate the activity of avelumab
      (MSB0010718C) in patients with metastatic or locally advanced urothelial cancer considered
      unfit to cisplatin-based chemotherapy, to be conducted in conformance with Good Clinical
      Practices.

      Cisplatin-unfit patients will be defined if at least one of these characteristics is present:

        1. ECOG-Performance status = 2;

        2. Creatinine Clearance < 60 ml/min;

        3. Grade 2 or worse peripheral neuropathy or hearing loss;

        4. Previous treatment with cisplatin for adjuvant intent in six months before the
           progression of disease.
